Environmental Mechanics: The Deep Water
The docks have no railings.
Falling In: If a character or enemy is shoved (Might vs. Might) or knocked back, they fall into the deep water.
The Penalty: Falling deals no damage, but the water is cold and dark. Climbing back onto the dock requires a Move Action and a Standard Athletics (Might) check.
Success: They climb up but lose their Major Action for the turn (shivering/coughing).
Failure: They remain in the water, treading water.
Effect on Enemies: If a pirate falls in, they are effectively removed from combat for 2 rounds as they swim to a ladder.


Player Approaches
Option A: Stealth (The Assassin's Route)
The Challenge: The Lookout has a clear line of sight.
The Solution: A synchronized shot. If the party can take out the Lookout silently (one shot kill or sleep spell) before he shouts, the two guards below can be ambushed with Advantage.
Mechanic: Agility (Stealth) vs. the Lookout's Guile (12).
Option B: Social (The Bluff)
The Challenge: Walking up openly.
The Solution: Wearing the clothes of a sailor or pirate (perhaps using a disguise kit or Illusion magic).
Dialogue: "Relief crew! Captain Valen sent us to take over the watch. You boys are wanted in the galley."
Mechanic: Guile (Deception) vs. the Sentries' Guile (10).
Success: The guards grumble but leave, opening the gate for the party. The Lookout stays up top but ignores them.
Failure: "I didn't hear no bell. And I don't know your face. Draw steel!"


Option C: Assault (The Brute Force)
The Challenge: Charging the gate.
The Tactics: The Lookout rains arrows while the Sentries block the narrow walkway (choke point), preventing the party from swarming them. Players can use Shield Bash to knock the Sentries into the water to clear the path instantly.
Loot & Aftermath
On the Table: 45 Gold (Gambling pot), a half-empty bottle of rum (heals 2 HP, -1 Intelligence/Guile for 1 hour).
The Lookout: Has a Potion of Minor Healing.
The Gate: It is barred from the inside but easily lifted once the guards are dealt with.
Transition:
Beyond the gate, the wooden walkway becomes precarious, leading toward the massive iron chain blocking the waterway.

Section 2: The Boom Chain (The Puzzle)
The Setting
The party advances past the checkpoint. The cavern widens, revealing the pirate fleetΓÇöor rather, the wreckage of it. Several smaller ships are docked, but the massive, stolen East Empire galleon, The Red Sabre, is visible in the distance, grounded on a sandbar deep in the cave.
However, the path forward is blocked by a massive fortification designed to stop ships.
Read Aloud:
"The wooden walkway ends at a stone platform overlooking the main channel. Stretching across the water, blocking the way to the inner grotto, is a colossal iron chain. Each link is the size of a manΓÇÖs torso, rusted and slick with algae.
This is a boom chainΓÇöa defensive barrier raised to smash the hulls of invading ships. Currently, it is raised taut above the water, acting as a wall of iron. To reach the Red Sabre where Captain Valen waits, you must cross the gap.
The drawbridge that normally spans the water is raised, its heavy timbers pointing toward the ceiling. The mechanism to lower it is on the other side, currently guarded by nothing but the silence of the cave.
You have three options: Force the chain, shoot the release, or brave the walk."
The Challenge: Crossing the Gap
The party must find a way to lower the bridge or cross the water without alerting the main camp.
Solution A: The ArcherΓÇÖs Shot (Precision)
The Target: A thick rope holding a counterweight on the far side of the bridge. It is frayed and old.
The Mechanic: A Standard Archery (Agility) attack roll.
Success: The arrow severs the rope. The counterweight crashes down, and the bridge slams into place with a loud THUD.
Complication (Roll equal to TN): The rope snaps, but the bridge jams halfway down. Characters must make a Standard Agility check to jump the remaining gap.
Failure: The arrow misses or hits a metal fitting with a loud CLANG, alerting the sentries in the next section.


Solution B: The StrongmanΓÇÖs Winch (Brute Force)
The Target: On the party's side, there is a secondary, rusted emergency winch. It looks seized by salt and time.
The Mechanic: A Hard (-2 Penalty) Might check to force the rusted gears to turn.
Success: With a groan of tortured metal, the chain slackens, lowering into the water. The party can walk across the submerged chain (wet, but safe).
Failure: The winch handle snaps off loudly. This path is now closed.


Solution C: The Tightrope Walk (Agility)
The Target: The chain itself. It is suspended five feet above the water. A character can attempt to walk across the slick, rounded links.
The Mechanic: A Hard (-2 Penalty) Agility check.
Success: The character dances across the chain and reaches the other side, where they can manually lower the bridge lever for the rest of the party.
Failure: The character slips and falls into the water with a splash. They must swim to the other side (losing time/stealth) or climb back up.


The Complication: The Hidden Sentry
If the party makes any loud noise (failed check, bridge slamming down), a door on the far side opens.
Read Aloud (If Alerted):
"The door on the far platform bangs open. A pirate mage, bleary-eyed and holding a half-eaten apple, stumbles out. 'Who's making that racket? Valen's trying to sleep!'"
