Section 5: The CaptainΓÇÖs Quarters (The Trap & The Reward)
The Setting
The heavy oak door to the captainΓÇÖs cabin swings open. Unlike the damp, rotting cave outside, this room smells of expensive mahogany, beeswax, and stolen perfume. It is a showcase of pirate vanityΓÇöplush rugs from Hammerfell, tapestries from High Rock, and a massive desk carved from blackwood.
At the foot of the bed sits a heavy, iron-bound chest. It looks sturdy, inviting... and dangerous.
Read Aloud:
"The silence in the captain's quarters is a welcome relief after the chaos of the deck. This room is a hoarder's palace of stolen luxury. It seems Captain Valen spent his coin on comfort.
On the desk lies a scattered collection of maps and a leather-bound shipΓÇÖs log. But the true prize sits at the foot of the bed: the shipΓÇÖs strongbox. It is reinforced with heavy iron bands, and the keyhole is surrounded by a strange, serrated metal dial resembling a serpent's mouth."
The Final Challenge: The Serpent's Snap
Captain Valen was paranoid. He knew his crew might try to rob him while he slept. The chest is locked, but it is also booby-trapped. Using the key found on Valen's body will unlock the lid, but turning it without disarming the mechanism triggers the trap.
Step 1: Investigation (The Warning)
A player who inspects the chest before blindly inserting the key can make a Standard Guile (Investigation) check.
Success: They notice faint scratches on the floor around the chest and a tension in the lid's hinges. The lock mechanism is rigged to a spring-loaded blade inside the rim.
Failure: It looks like a sturdy, ordinary chest.
Step 2: The Solution (Two Paths)
The Mechanical Disarm: A character with steady hands can attempt a Hard (-2) Agility (Thievery) check to slide a dagger or shim under the lid and jam the spring mechanism before unlocking it.
The Intellectual Solution (The Logbook): A player who reads the Ship's Log on the desk before touching the chest finds a cryptic note on the inside cover: "Twice left, once right, then the snake sleeps."
If the players rotate the serrated dial around the keyhole according to the instructions (2 left, 1 right) before inserting the key, the trap disengages with a soft click. No roll required.


The Trigger (Failure or Carelessness)
If the players insert the key without disarming the trap (or fail the Agility roll):
Effect: As the key turns, a rusted, jagged scythe blade snaps out from the front of the chest at shin-level.
Damage: The character standing in front of the chest takes 4 Slashing Damage and must make a Standard Might check or suffer Bleeding (1 damage per turn) until healed.
The Treasure Hoard
Once the trap is bypassed or triggered, the lid creaks open, revealing the hoard.
