Here is Part IV: The Resolution and the GM Cheat Sheet to finalize the adventure module.

Part IV: The Resolution
The Escape
With the loot secured and the captain dead, the remaining pirates (if any survive) flee into the deeper tunnels of the grotto. The party can take the skiff back out to the entrance where Orthus waits.
The Handover
The return journey is calm, the sun beginning to set over the Sea of Ghosts, painting the water in gold and crimson.
Read Aloud:
"Orthus is pacing frantic circles on the rocky shelf when you return. He nearly falls into the water in his haste to greet you.
'You're alive! And the... the item? Do you have it?'
When you produce the amulet, his knees actually buckle with relief. He clutches it with trembling hands, checking it for scratches. 'Oh, thank the Eight. Thank you. You have saved my life, and my pension.'"
The Payment
Orthus is true to his word.
Gold: He hands over a heavy sack containing 500 Gold per player.
Bonus: If the players mention the traitor in his office (from the logbook), Orthus goes pale but nods grimly. "I suspected as much. I will handle it. Take this for the intelligence." He adds a Letter of Credit worth 100 Gold at any East Empire Company warehouse.
Advancement
Experience: Each player gains 1 Advancement Point (AP) for completing the adventure.
Reputation: The party gains the favor of a mid-level bureaucrat. While not a Jarl, Orthus can be a useful contact for smuggling, travel, or trade information in the future.

