The Situation
You are a crew of freelance problem-solvers currently stuck in Solitude. The capital is beautiful, but it is expensive. Your coin purses are light, your tab at the Winking Skeever is growing, and you need a job that pays now.
You answered a discreet posting from an East Empire Company administrator named Orthus Endario. He didn't meet you in an office; he asked you to meet him on a freezing, salt-sprayed pier at dawn. He looks desperate. Desperate men pay well.
Your Goal: Hear him out, take the contract, and get paid.

